What are Toasts?

Brief pop-up messages in Android apps.
Provide temporary feedback to users.
Syntax for Creating a Toast:

Toast.makeText(context, "Your Message", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
Replace "Your Message" with the actual message.
Use Toast.LENGTH_SHORT or Toast.LENGTH_LONG for duration.
Customization Options:

Change message, duration, and position on the screen.
Best Practices:

Keep messages concise and clear.
Avoid overwhelming users with excessive Toasts.
Ensure visibility and legibility, especially for accessibility.
Next Steps:

Practice creating and customizing Toasts.
Document learnings on GitHub.
Integrate Toasts into app for better user interaction.
